Wasn't 100% sure what to expect, but they were actually pretty good action/thrillers.  Whereas the first movie takes place entirely in a home, the second movie ventures outside and around a city, and you get to see a lot more of how the Purge interacts in the world.  A bit heavy-handed in some respects with the classism, they were both thoroughly entertaining, and if you want a little thought experiment while watching some decent flicks, I would highly recommend these.  I enjoyed the second movie more, but that's because I found the main male character more relatable, and the story far more interesting.  Really looking forward to picking up the third movie.

Difficult to judge movies nowadays. Having never seen The Purge or the sequel I wasn't sure what type of movie these would turn to be. I had to say I was surprised and both movies were excellent. A rare sequel that improves on the original. The content was excellent and the concept along with the characters were enjoyable. A great collection all in all.

I really preferred The Purge more so over the second one. The first movie was very sociologically relevant focusing on economic systems, class, class division, and discrimination based on all the above. It was a good movie. The second one was more entertainment building off of a franchise. These movies were recommended to me by my sociology students.
